      "side": 1,
      "message": "I hadn\u0027t really thought about that since until I just rebased SK_ABORT was using SkUNREACHABLE. I do kinda like being able to use FAST_FAIL_INVALID_ARG here instead of FAST_FAIL_FATAL_APP_EXIT since SkUNREACHABLE is generally used for \u0027unexpected input\u0027 and SK_ABORT for \u0027things didn\u0027t work\u0027 but that\u0027s a bit subtle. Funneling through SK_ABORT would actually simplify some things in Chromium though (we\u0027d log a fatal error and abort from Chromium\u0027s logging abort mechanism).\n\nInterestingly the Windows bots here on PS3 complain\n\n    warning C4715: \u0027GrSwizzle::CToI\u0027: not all control paths return a value\n\nwhich is still technically true, since some control paths don\u0027t return at all.",
